AttributeSubGroup.AttributeDescription: CPUE thresholds - CPUEs above or below this tonnes/days-at-sea for a target species will cause an effort shift

Proportion of effort above which exploratory fishing will occur in nearby cells
Incremental proportional change in CPUE if pass CPUE threshold (i.e. 1+prop on way up and 1-prop on way down)
Effort caps - size in total days at sea allowed for the entire fleet for the year. Only need be > 0 if flagcap set = 1

Vectors indicating which ports each fishery can operate from initially (other ports may be activated using the flagnewport option in the switch and flag section at the top of the file). 1 = from the port, 0 = not active from the port. The list of ports are listed at the top of the parameter file - there must be as many entries as there are ports (K_num_ports)

AttributeSubGroup.AttributeDescription: Port location and timing parameters - there must be as many entries as there are ports (K_num_ports).

Attribute.AttributeDescription: X coordinate (in metres as in model space)
Y coordinate (in metres as in model space)

The proportion of the population who fish recreationally
Harvest strategy tier for RBC setting (only >0 if dynamically setting TACs). 0 = whinging harvest strategy, 1-4 = tier 1-4, tier 5 = ecological indicator based

Trip Limit parameters - not necessarily associated with a TAC, this is a limit on total catch (in kg) of the group for that fishery per seven day period (if there are shorter trips in reality, sum over these trips to get 7 days duration and use the sum as the limit here). Individual trip limits (in tonnes) per fishery per group
Total allowable catch (TAC in tonnes) per fishery per group

Bimonthly trip limts (like in the US) - if you want to use these (currently only with Dan Holland economic model) then to enter them, fill in TAC above for entire year and then enter the proportion in each bimonthly period in the vectors below. You must do one set for each management region (currently allows for 3 management regions)
Whether the fishery must land all catch of quota groups regardless of quota remaining (i.e. no discards allowed if over quota).

True if the group is part of the regional quoa member
Whether TACs use stock based regional TAC (0) or management area regional TAC (1)

Proportional distribution of overall TACs across management regions - this read in is currently only used by the Dan Holland model (the standard regional management model has the management zones mapped to the reproductive stocks of the individual groups and so calculates the distribution directly rather than using this read-in value
Basket quotas flag
Number of each groups in the quota

Basket quota membership (entries should be the guild id numbers (see top of file for values) for each species in the basket other than the basket_TACFxx group (i.e. in basketTAC_FPS do not put the code for FPS, only the species other than FPS in the basket with FPS). For an entry of 'no other species' (i.e. single species quota) put in a single entry with value -1. Array length should be BasketSize for each species.
Maximum number of companions in a companion TAC

Identity of companions in companion TAC - for all entries must have as many entries as for max_co_sp. If there are not enough (or any) companions then for all extra entries enter companion as -1. For those WITH companions entries to the ID numbers of the companion then enter -1 to fill up the rest of the array. For example if max_co_sp = 2 and the companions for FXX were FPS and FVV co_sp_FXX 2 2 4
Type of companion TAC (0 = weakest link dictates quota, 1 = strongest link dictates quota)
Whether multi-year TACs are one total for the entire period or if it is annual quota to track just not doing an assessment for x years
Multi-year TAC - time (in years between resets)
Vectors indicating ratio of catch of companion group identified above with each group in each fishery
Vectors indicating ratio of catch of second companion group identified above with each group in each fishery

Proportion of spawning grounds closed when trading off vs TAC reduction of the group for that fishery per seven day period (if there are shorter trips in reality, sum over these trips to get 7 days duration and use the sum as the limit here). Individual trip limits (in tonnes) per fishery per group.
Identification of groups of concern - those groups regarded as threatened. If the stock of these groups falls too low then fisheries may be closed. A 1=threatened, 0=ignore
